text.section:
A proposal for the designation of a heritage area as a recognized heritage area shall:
Be previously approved and submitted by the governing bodies of all of the local jurisdictions located within the specific boundaries proposed for the recognized heritage area;
To the maximum extent practicable, be developed in consultation with affected State agencies;
Specify the boundaries for the recognized heritage area;
Identify the local entity responsible for coordinating development of the management plan required under § 13-1111 of this subtitle;
Describe the cultural, historic, and natural resources which contribute to the special character of the heritage area;
Specify the general goals and objectives for the preservation, development, and management of the heritage area;
Identify the types of public and private uses to be accommodated in the heritage area;
Describe strategies for encouraging and accommodating visitation to and compatible economic development of the heritage area;
Provide an economic overview of the long and short term costs and benefits related to the development of the heritage area; and
Describe the techniques and means to be instituted by the local jurisdictions to assure the long term preservation and protection of the cultural, historic, and natural resources within the heritage area, including zoning, subdivision controls, and other growth management techniques.
